Here's a possible implementation of the `show` method for the `FloatWithUnits` struct:
```go
type FloatWithUnits struct {
value float64
unit string
}
func (f FloatWithUnits) show() String {
return fmt.Sprintf("%.2f %s", f.value, f.unit)
}
```
The `fmt.Sprintf` function allows us to format the output string with the desired precision and concatenate the value and unit using a space as specified in the prompt.
